    "34553428": {
      "title": "Architects at the bacterial surface -sortases and the assembly of pili with isopeptide bonds",
      "abstract": "Sortases are enzymes that produce transpeptide bonds which can either link proteins to the cell wall or introduce intermolecular bonds in pili. Schneewind and colleagues describe how these enzymes function on a molecular level and provide an overview of the pili on which they function."
